<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-236-194  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 236 194.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  April 24 1989 v6 n16 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Users should be wary of new solutions to old problems. (ISDN)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Johnston, Mary.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ISDN technology is being implemented without considering whetherit can actually improve current conditions.andP;  The approach manymajor ISDN purveyors take is geared toward using the technology asa voice communications enhancement, ignoring the possibilities forimproved data communications, more integrated network managementand improvements to the corporation's bottom line.andP;  The successfulselling of ISDN will require a complete change in the psychologyunderlying the marketing and application development approaches.andO;Users want technologies that are effective business tools and thatsupport a broad range of requirements profitably.andP;  ISDN proponentsmust make a strong case to senior management that ISDN is astrategic business tool that can be used to market the corporationto its employees, distributors and customers.andP;  Guidelines forchoosing ISDN vendors are also included.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ISDNMarketingUser NeedsStrategic PlanningApplicationsGuidelines.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>